detaileddescription.para: This module loads a deduplicated model representation described by model.dedup.json and maps the backing binary blobs (defaults/exceptions/masks) using mmap(2).

The loader exposes a uniform ie_weights_dedup_get_weight_view() API returning an ie_weight_view_t that can represent either:
A direct contiguous tensor view, or
A deduplicated tensor view referencing (defaults + mask + exceptions).

Mask semantics:
bit=0 => use defaults value
bit=1 => consume next value from exceptions stream and override
For int4 tensors, elements are nibbles (4-bit values) in row-major order.
